statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.name: defensiveRebounds
statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: Stony Brook 80, Mount Ida College 43
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Bryan Dougher scored 21 of his 24 points in the second half as Stony Brook overpowered Mount Ida College 80-43 on Sunday. The Seawolves (1-1) led 34-29 at halftime, then blew out the Mustangs 46-14 in the second half. Mount Ida, a Division III school counting the game as an exhibition, took an 8-2 lead and led 27-23 with 3:08 to go before halftime. Stony Brook closed out the period on an 11-2 run, then opened the second half on an 11-0 tear. The Mustangs were scoreless the last 3:58. The Seawolves shot 45.1 percent from the field (23 of 51) compared to 27.4 percent (17 of 62) for Mount Ida. Stony Brook also hit 24 of 31 free throws -- 16 of 20 in the first half as the Mustangs committed 15 fouls. The Mustangs were just 1 of 6 from the foul line. Al Rapier added 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Seawolves. Isiah Benjamin led the Mustangs with 13 points.
